Build Identifier: Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 5.1; rv:2.0) Gecko/20100101 Firefox/4.0

An image that is also a link (i.e., with HTML &lt;A HREF=...&gt;&lt;IMG SRC=...&gt;&lt;/A&gt;),
should by default be drawn with a border around in link color, so that the user
knows that it is a link. However, beginning with version 4, Firefox has not been
doing this.


Reproducible: Always

Steps to Reproduce:
1. Direct Firefox 4 to a Web page that has clickable images that do not specify
border options, such as the specified URL.
2. Observe clickable images.

Actual Results:  
Images do not have borders.

Expected Results:  
Images should have borders.</thetext>
